WEBVTT

NOTE
House Fire Simulation — Untreated vs AF31 Treated Structure
Duration: ~8 minutes 59 seconds

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:15.000
[Two residential structures shown side by side — left labeled "Untreated House", right labeled "AF31 Treated House"]

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:35.000
[On-screen text: "Equal amounts of lighter fluid and kindling were applied to both structures"]

00:00:35.000 --> 00:01:10.000
[Firefighter ignites the untreated structure with a torch — it catches fire immediately and flames spread rapidly]

00:01:10.000 --> 00:02:00.000
[Untreated house burns intensely, structure consumed by fire, thick smoke rising]

00:02:00.000 --> 00:03:00.000
[Camera shifts to AF31 treated structure — firefighter applies same torch and lighter fluid]

00:03:00.000 --> 00:04:00.000
[AF31 treated structure resists ignition — flames do not spread beyond the initial contact point]

00:04:00.000 --> 00:05:00.000
[On-screen text: "Once the fuel burned out, AF31 chemistry extinguished the fire"]

00:05:00.000 --> 00:06:00.000
[AF31 treated structure: fire self-extinguishes after initial fuel burns out — no sustained combustion]

00:06:00.000 --> 00:07:00.000
[Side-by-side comparison: untreated house fully destroyed, treated house structure remains intact]

00:07:00.000 --> 00:08:00.000
[Aerial and close-up shots show the charred ruins of the untreated house versus the preserved framing of the AF31 treated house]

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:59.000
[Final comparison of debris and remaining structure — AF31 treated home withstood the fire simulation]
